page.title: 10Streets of Strensall
page.content: (Army camp streets excluded).Whilst a very old village{(17th century houses) Strensall has seen{extensive housing {development}over the 15 year period to 1985. Current building is scheduled to 1990.Pre-1930 Strensall had about 12 roads, since 1965 estate developments have boosted this to 56.Street names declared by the post office but as yet unbuilt indicate 78 roads by 1990.The original village included The Village, Church Lane and West End.Moor Lane and Princess Road were developed before 1930.Northfields was built in the mid 1950's.Rapid development began in the mid 1960's (Oak Tree Close estate).The extensive developments south of West End and West of Moor Lane towards the River Foss appeared after the mid 70's.To date all development has been to housing.No{new shop}has been built outside the original village locality.
